<h3>4. Collaboration and Peer Learning</h3>
<p>Collaborative projects are powerful. A technically inclined student can handle the &ldquo;doing&rdquo; part (coding, analysis, simulations), while another student focuses on synthesizing the written work. Through collaboration, both sets of learners sharpen weaker skills by exposure to the other&rsquo;s strengths.</p>
<p>Furthermore, online communities forums, Discord groups, and course discussion boards act as dynamic spaces where technical and writing questions are solved interactively.</p>
